Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.12,0:00:23.69,Dialogue,C,0000,0000,0000,,Today's deduction is really shocking.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.69,0:00:25.19,Dialogue,C,0000,0000,0000,,The trick uses a normal time difference in sledding...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.19,0:00:26.96,Dialogue,C,0000,0000,0000,,to create the perfect alibi!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.96,0:00:28.38,Dialogue,C,0000,0000,0000,,Seeing through to the one and only truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.38,0:00:30.20,Dialogue,C,0000,0000,0000,,I look like a child but have the intellect of an adult.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.20,0:00:31.88,Dialogue,C,0000,0000,0000,,My name is Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.75,0:01:59.17,Dialogue,Title,0000,0000,0000,,Case of the Furisode at the Hidden Hot Spring,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.30,0:02:00.06,Dialogue,Title,0000,0000,0000,,Part 2!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.80,0:02:07.77,Dialogue,O,0000,0000,0000,,Asuka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} went into the open-air hot spring around 10pm.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.77,0:02:11.27,Dialogue,O,0000,0000,0000,,Ema{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} went to the garden's shrine around 10:30pm.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.24,0:02:14.78,Dialogue,O,0000,0000,0000,,Both of them were killed by this holy knife.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.18,0:02:18.26,Dialogue Top,O,0000,0000,0000,,This knife was found in the hot spring, which means...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.26,0:02:22.74,Dialogue Top,O,0000,0000,0000,,the culprit murdered Ema{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} first, then went after Asuka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.74,0:02:25.83,Dialogue,M,0000,0000,0000,,Furthermore, the shrine, which is located in the garden,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.83,0:02:28.53,Dialogue,M,0000,0000,0000,,has footprints only from Ema{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s boots.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.54,0:02:32.46,Dialogue,M,0000,0000,0000,,In order to get to the hot spring, one would have to go through the recreation area,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.46,0:02:34.71,Dialogue,M,0000,0000,0000,,but people were there from around 10:30pm onwards.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.06,0:02:35.94,Dialogue,O,0000,0000,0000,,My, my...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.21,0:02:38.01,Dialogue,O,0000,0000,0000,,They're both locked rooms.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.01,0:02:39.63,Dialogue,H,0000,0000,0000,,They visited Furisode!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.63,0:02:43.51,Dialogue,H,0000,0000,0000,,Sakurako{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} visited Furisode and wanted revenge on those two people!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.51,0:02:45.11,Dialogue,O,0000,0000,0000,,Sakurako{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.11,0:02:46.77,Dialogue,O,0000,0000,0000,,Who is she?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.32,0:02:48.62,Dialogue Top,H,0000,0000,0000,,She's my senpai from my university.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.23,0:02:53.44,Dialogue Top,H,0000,0000,0000,,Those two framed her of running secret drug-dealing operations.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.44,0:02:55.36,Dialogue,H,0000,0000,0000,,Because of that, she committed suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.36,0:02:59.07,Dialogue,O,0000,0000,0000,,The "two" as in the murdered, Asuka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and Ema{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}? {changed: "Does "both of them" mean the victims" to "The "two" as in the murdered"}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.49,0:03:00.74,Dialogue,H,0000,0000,0000,,Exactly.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.74,0:03:02.20,Dialogue,H,0000,0000,0000,,That's why...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.20,0:03:03.78,Dialogue,H,0000,0000,0000,,That's why Senpai had...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.62,0:03:05.91,Dialogue,?,0000,0000,0000,,Officer Masaki.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.82,0:03:12.32,Dialogue,?,0000,0000,0000,,In the shrine, one of the corpse's earrings is missing.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.83,0:03:14.84,Dialogue,?,0000,0000,0000,,This is the one that's left.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.84,0:03:17.17,Dialogue,Y,0000,0000,0000,,That's... a brand name.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.71,0:03:21.93,Dialogue,Y,0000,0000,0000,,Just a single one of them costs about 200 thousand yen.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.66,0:03:24.79,Dialogue,?,0000,0000,0000,,Then a pair costs 400 thousand yen...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.79,0:03:29.25,Dialogue,O,0000,0000,0000,,Even though it's not cheap, it can't be the only reason to kill someone.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.85,0:03:35.11,Dialogue,Y,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, yeah! I think Harumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} has a pendant of the same brand.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.82,0:03:37.33,Dialogue,H,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. But...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.33,0:03:40.63,Dialogue,H,0000,0000,0000,,Ema{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} seemed unhappy when she saw me wear the pendant, so I immediately took it off. {changed: "it" to "them"}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.08,0:03:45.16,Dialogue,?,0000,0000,0000,,I see. Other than that, we found this in Ema{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s coat pocket.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.79,0:03:48.14,Dialogue,?,0000,0000,0000,,And the furisodes and obis left in the scene...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.14,0:03:50.94,Dialogue,?,0000,0000,0000,,were those kept in the storage room of this hotel,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.94,0:03:53.29,Dialogue,?,0000,0000,0000,,which is normally left unlocked.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.85,0:03:55.82,Dialogue,O,0000,0000,0000,,So anyone could've taken them out?{changed: "Therefore, anyone is able to take them out." to current; tone not write}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.83,0:03:59.17,Dialogue,?,0000,0000,0000,,The culprit most likely placed them there beforehand.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.78,0:04:03.88,Dialogue,O,0000,0000,0000,,Now, let's review what each of you did last night.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.88,0:04:04.84,Dialogue,O,0000,0000,0000,,First off, Eri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.41,0:04:08.22,Dialogue,O,0000,0000,0000,,You went to the open-air hot spring around 9:30pm...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.22,0:04:09.22,Dialogue,O,0000,0000,0000,,and came out around 10pm.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.93,0:04:12.48,Dialogue,O,0000,0000,0000,,Asuka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} went into it afterwards.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.48,0:04:16.64,Dialogue,I,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, I went back to my room after that.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.64,0:04:19.61,Dialogue,I,0000,0000,0000,,I met Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and the others halfway, and we talked there.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.11,0:04:25.66,Dialogue,M,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I was thinking of asking Eri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} to have a drink at that time.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.57,0:04:28.26,Dialogue,O,0000,0000,0000,,Then?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.26,0:04:32.32,Dialogue,O,0000,0000,0000,,Yoriko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was starting to reorganize the content of the interview here at 9:30pm.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.32,0:04:33.37,Dialogue,O,0000,0000,0000,,This means...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.37,0:04:36.40,Dialogue,Y,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, I saw Eri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.40,0:04:40.71,Dialogue,Y,0000,0000,0000,,Five minutes later, I saw Ema{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} head toward the back door there.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.21,0:04:43.26,Dialogue,O,0000,0000,0000,,That's around 10:30pm.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.26,0:04:46.05,Dialogue,O,0000,0000,0000,,Did you see anyone else go to the back door?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.27,0:04:49.93,Dialogue,Y,0000,0000,0000,,No, no one.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.35,0:04:53.93,Dialogue,O,0000,0000,0000,,At that time, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and the others went to the open-air hot spring.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.37,0:04:56.94,Dialogue,O,0000,0000,0000,,However, there was a "rented out" sign on the door of the women's hot spring.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.28,0:04:59.91,Dialogue,O,0000,0000,0000,,Moreover, the door was locked.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.91,0:05:01.65,Dialogue,O,0000,0000,0000,,So then, the two of you went back to the recreation room.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.65,0:05:03.11,Dialogue,R,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.46,0:05:08.11,Dialogue,O,0000,0000,0000,,Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, did anything strange happen while bathing?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.11,0:05:09.37,Dialogue,C,0000,0000,0000,,There was.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.50,0:05:13.38,Dialogue,C,0000,0000,0000,,We heard a strange splashing sound from the women's hot spring.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.76,0:05:16.32,Dialogue,O,0000,0000,0000,,What time was it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.79,0:05:19.00,Dialogue,C,0000,0000,0000,,It was definitely around 10:50pm.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.39,0:05:21.36,Dialogue,?,0000,0000,0000,,Wasn't that the time of the crime?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.36,0:05:22.56,Dialogue,O,0000,0000,0000,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.56,0:05:26.26,Dialogue,C,0000,0000,0000,,But it was only the splashing sound and no scream.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.26,0:05:27.01,Dialogue,C,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that strange? {changed: "We didn't hear any screams." to current}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.16,0:05:33.18,Dialogue,M,0000,0000,0000,,That's because the culprit used the stun gun to make her faint before she screamed. {change: took out "right"}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.59,0:05:34.81,Dialogue,C,0000,0000,0000,,Really? {changed: from "Was it like that?" to current}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.29,0:05:40.11,Dialogue,M,0000,0000,0000,,Of course! You little brat, don't interrupt the investigation!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.11,0:05:46.08,Dialogue,O,0000,0000,0000,,Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and Harumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} didn't leave the recreation room?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.08,0:05:50.12,Dialogue,H,0000,0000,0000,,No, I forgot to wear my contact lenses,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.12,0:05:53.66,Dialogue,H,0000,0000,0000,,so I went back to my room for about 10 minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.00,0:05:55.41,Dialogue,O,0000,0000,0000,,I understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.41,0:05:58.79,Dialogue,O,0000,0000,0000,,And no one else passed the recreation room during that time?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.19,0:06:00.21,Dialogue,R,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.84,0:06:03.77,Dialogue,O,0000,0000,0000,,Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} came out of the men's hot spring around 11pm.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.77,0:06:07.22,Dialogue,O,0000,0000,0000,,Eri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and Yoriko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} were here discussing at that time.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.65,0:06:09.70,Dialogue,O,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, what about Bandou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.70,0:06:13.39,Dialogue,B,0000,0000,0000,,I joined their discussion around 11:15pm.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.47,0:06:18.98,Dialogue,O,0000,0000,0000,,And that's when Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and the others found Asuka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s body in the hot spring.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.74,0:06:21.85,Dialogue,O,0000,0000,0000,,About the dolls of Furisode-Hannya:
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.85,0:06:24.69,Dialogue,O,0000,0000,0000,,They weren't on the ground in the beginning, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.69,0:06:26.94,Dialogue,R,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, there's no doubt about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.25,0:06:30.53,Dialogue,O,0000,0000,0000,,Next, Ema{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s body was found in the shrine.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.93,0:06:33.33,Dialogue,C,0000,0000,0000,,Why did Ema{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} go to the shrine? {changed: "does" to "did"}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.56,0:06:35.95,Dialogue,O,0000,0000,0000,,Good question.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.42,0:06:37.98,Dialogue,O,0000,0000,0000,,This is the reason:
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.98,0:06:40.71,Dialogue,O,0000,0000,0000,,"Ema{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, there's something I would like to talk to you about in secret.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.11,0:06:42.37,Dialogue,O,0000,0000,0000,,Tonight at 10:30pm,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.37,0:06:44.55,Dialogue,O,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be waiting for you at the shrine in the backyard.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.55,0:06:45.30,Dialogue,O,0000,0000,0000,,- Bandou."
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.30,0:06:47.04,Dialogue,B,0000,0000,0000,,H-How can that be?! {changed: "It's impossible" to current}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.04,0:06:49.26,Dialogue,B,0000,0000,0000,,I never wrote that letter! {changed: "this" to "that"}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.26,0:06:53.38,Dialogue,O,0000,0000,0000,,You don't have an alibi before 11:15pm.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.38,0:06:57.68,Dialogue,B,0000,0000,0000,,B-But I don't have a motive to murder them!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.88,0:07:01.10,Dialogue,O,0000,0000,0000,,Now, the only one who seems to have a motive...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.10,0:07:02.69,Dialogue,O,0000,0000,0000,,appears to be Harumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.69,0:07:04.48,Dialogue,H,0000,0000,0000,,What?! I... {changed: "How can it be" to "What"}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.48,0:07:08.44,Dialogue,O,0000,0000,0000,,You felt hatred toward both of them because of your senpai who had committed suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.44,0:07:12.95,Dialogue,O,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, you don't have an alibi during the time you went back to your room for your contact lenses.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.95,0:07:15.62,Dialogue,H,0000,0000,0000,,I... I'd never do that!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.29,0:07:18.02,Thoughts,C,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}No matter who the culprit is,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.02,0:07:20.62,Thoughts,C,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}if the mystery of the sealed-room isn't solved, we won't get anywhere. {changed: from "I'm unable to reveal the mystery of the secret room, nothing can be done to the culprit." to current}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.38,0:07:24.79,Thoughts,C,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}If both of them were murdered by different weapons,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.79,0:07:26.55,Thoughts,C,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}it'd be a bit easier to justify.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.38,0:07:32.44,Thoughts,C,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Besides, why did the culprit make the scene look like what had been described in the Furisode-Hannya legend? {changed: "does" to "did" delete "want to"}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.74,0:07:39.18,Dialogue,?,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you. Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.18,0:07:42.31,Dialogue,?,0000,0000,0000,,Here's the delivery.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.48,0:07:46.36,Dialogue,O,0000,0000,0000,,It's finally here, the autopsy report.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.36,0:07:49.36,Dialogue,?,0000,0000,0000,,The weapon which killed both of them is the holy knife.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.80,0:07:51.50,Dialogue,O,0000,0000,0000,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.50,0:07:53.18,Dialogue,O,0000,0000,0000,,If the weapon had been different,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.18,0:07:55.12,Dialogue,O,0000,0000,0000,,this problem would've been easier to handle. {changed: "would be" to "would've been"}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.18,0:07:57.83,Dialogue,C,0000,0000,0000,,So the weapons were the same...{changed: "It's really like this..." to current}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.46,0:08:02.08,Dialogue,?,0000,0000,0000,,That bandana has traces of only Ema{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.57,0:08:06.34,Dialogue,?,0000,0000,0000,,Also, the dolls from the scene, the Holy Mansion and other areas,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.34,0:08:13.22,Dialogue,?,0000,0000,0000,,and Ema{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s letter: We couldn't find any fingerprints or information that related to the culprit on them.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.85,0:08:15.97,Dialogue,O,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks for your effort.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.93,0:08:19.15,Dialogue,?,0000,0000,0000,,Then, I'll take my leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.71,0:08:21.98,Dialogue,O,0000,0000,0000,,This really is troublesome, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.11,0:08:25.60,Dialogue,M,0000,0000,0000,,No lead, huh? {changed: "Nothing's being found, is it?" to current}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.60,0:08:29.93,Radio,M,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Next is about the children's ice-sledding competition.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.93,0:08:32.40,Radio,?,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Get out of my way! Get out of my way! {Any other shorter term for this?}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.40,0:08:33.57,Dialogue,R,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like fun. {changed: "It looks funny." to current}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.57,0:08:35.32,Dialogue,C,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? What does? {changed: "What's" to "What"}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.32,0:08:38.20,Dialogue,R,0000,0000,0000,,Those kids. The children on TV.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.35,0:08:40.91,Radio,?,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Get out of my way! Get out of my way!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.28,0:08:42.66,Thoughts,C,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Oh, I see!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.61,0:08:50.79,Thoughts,C,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}That's why the footprints were... {changed: "are" to "were"}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.79,0:08:53.59,Thoughts,C,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}The truth of this matter's starting to get clearer. {changed: "It's starting to get clearer, the truth of this matter." to current}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.90,0:09:03.56,Thoughts,C,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}The snow over here is about 15cm deep. {changed: "thick" to "deep"}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.91,0:09:26.96,Thoughts,C,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Here it... can be pressed down about 5cm at the most.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.46,0:09:29.46,Thoughts,C,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}15cm and 5cm.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.09,0:09:31.71,Thoughts,C,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}But, why did that person...? {changed: "does" to "did"}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.23,0:09:42.89,Dialogue,R,0000,0000,0000,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, where did you go?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.52,0:09:46.02,Dialogue,C,0000,0000,0000,,Just took a walk around here.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.71,0:09:50.26,Thoughts,C,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Tokyo First?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.43,0:09:53.11,Thoughts,C,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Is Bandou{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10}...?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.49,0:09:56.34,Thoughts,C,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Wait... Don't tell me that person...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.34,0:09:59.41,Dialogue,R,0000,0000,0000,,Wait! Why are your socks all wet?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.70,0:10:01.71,Dialogue,R,0000,0000,0000,,Go dry them up faster.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.85,0:10:02.76,Dialogue,C,0000,0000,0000,,Hold on. Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-neechan{\r}, wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.27,0:10:06.45,Thoughts,C,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}The culprit is that person.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.45,0:10:08.74,Thoughts,C,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}It's definitely that person!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.74,0:10:10.12,Thoughts,C,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}But... why?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.39,0:10:17.55,Thoughts,C,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}If that person is the culprit,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.51,0:10:21.22,Thoughts,C,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}when and how did they put the doll here?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.23,0:10:24.36,Flashback,R,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}What is this thing? {changed: match ep 379}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.36,0:10:27.06,Flashback,H,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}That wasn't here earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.51,0:10:30.06,Flashback,R,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}It feels a little cold in my hands. Gives me the chills. {changed: to match ep 379}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.17,0:10:41.53,Thoughts,C,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}So, that's how it is... {changed: "I see, it's like this." to current}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.11,0:10:45.59,Dialogue,C,0000,0000,0000,,Taka{k}gi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.59,0:10:47.12,Dialogue,C,0000,0000,0000,,It's me, Mouri.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.50,0:10:52.25,Dialogue,C,0000,0000,0000,,Actually, I need you to help me investigate something.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.88,0:10:54.46,Dialogue,C,0000,0000,0000,,Ogura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.77,0:10:58.67,Dialogue,C,0000,0000,0000,,Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} needs you to do him a favor.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.67,0:11:01.68,Dialogue,G,0000,0000,0000,,Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}? Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.63,0:11:06.77,Thoughts,C,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}If my deduction is correct,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.77,0:11:08.77,Thoughts,C,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}that person must be...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.31,0:11:10.72,Dialogue,?,0000,0000,0000,,Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.72,0:11:13.77,Dialogue,?,0000,0000,0000,,You've gathered everyone here. What's going on? {changed: "Is there anything else?" to current}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.77,0:11:18.36,Dialogue,M,0000,0000,0000,,It's time to reveal the truth about this case, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.90,0:11:21.89,Dialogue,Y,0000,0000,0000,,You already know who the culprit is?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.89,0:11:23.32,Dialogue,B,0000,0000,0000,,Who is the culprit?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.82,0:11:26.70,Dialogue,M,0000,0000,0000,,Let me explain it in order. First,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.70,0:11:31.66,Dialogue,M,0000,0000,0000,,let's start off with where Ema{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was murdered: the mystery of the sealed-room, Furisode{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r}'s shrine. {changed: "Furisode-sama's shrine, the mysterious secret room" to current}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.32,0:11:33.77,Dialogue,M,0000,0000,0000,,Officer Masaki,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.77,0:11:37.69,Dialogue,M,0000,0000,0000,,can you turn on the digital camera that's on the trough?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.38,0:11:47.76,Dialogue,M,0000,0000,0000,,I kept thinking that something was wrong with this footprint left by boots.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.20,0:11:51.77,Dialogue,M,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't realize it until this morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.19,0:11:54.30,Dialogue,O,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong with this?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.30,0:11:56.98,Dialogue,M,0000,0000,0000,,The footprint is too shallow.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.33,0:12:00.97,Dialogue,M,0000,0000,0000,,Last night, when I reached the shrine,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.97,0:12:04.11,Dialogue,M,0000,0000,0000,,my feet were pressing about 7-8cm into the snow.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.30,0:12:08.88,Dialogue,M,0000,0000,0000,,In fact, it kept snowing after that.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.88,0:12:13.97,Dialogue,M,0000,0000,0000,,Ema{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, who went to the shrine that night around 10:30pm, wore boots that...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.97,0:12:18.92,Dialogue,M,0000,0000,0000,,should've gone in about 15cm.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.92,0:12:21.88,Dialogue,M,0000,0000,0000,,However, in reality, it's only 7-8cm at most.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.70,0:12:24.09,Dialogue,M,0000,0000,0000,,That's way too shallow.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.46,0:12:26.85,Dialogue,O,0000,0000,0000,,I see. Then what's the reason?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.31,0:12:29.56,Dialogue,M,0000,0000,0000,,It's because the footprints were pressed.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.82,0:12:31.99,Dialogue,O,0000,0000,0000,,Pressed? Weren't they pressed already?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.99,0:12:33.10,Dialogue,M,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.42,0:12:37.48,Dialogue,M,0000,0000,0000,,In order for Ema{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s footprints to not be covered by snow,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.18,0:12:41.42,Dialogue,M,0000,0000,0000,,the footprints from the back door to the shrine...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.42,0:12:44.04,Dialogue,M,0000,0000,0000,,were covered by towels.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.04,0:12:46.63,Dialogue,M,0000,0000,0000,,What would've happened if they weren't towels...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.63,0:12:48.83,Dialogue,M,0000,0000,0000,,but planks?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.83,0:12:52.20,Dialogue,M,0000,0000,0000,,The culprit wouldn't leave any footprints and could walk back and forth freely...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.75,0:12:55.67,Dialogue,M,0000,0000,0000,,from the back door to the shrine.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.01,0:12:58.67,Dialogue,Y,0000,0000,0000,,It's that simple?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.01,0:13:02.51,Dialogue,M,0000,0000,0000,,The tricks that cover people's intentions are just that simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.51,0:13:04.01,Dialogue,M,0000,0000,0000,,The culprit most likely... {changed: "Perhaps, the culprit" to current}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.92,0:13:08.09,Dialogue,M,0000,0000,0000,,prepared 2 pieces of wood, which were about 1 meter each.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.09,0:13:12.39,Dialogue,M,0000,0000,0000,,Then, taking turns covering Ema{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s footprints, walk to there.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.22,0:13:20.15,Dialogue,M,0000,0000,0000,,And then, using the same method, went back to the back door after murdering Ema{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.45,0:13:23.74,Dialogue,M,0000,0000,0000,,With these, the footprints would become more shallow,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.45,0:13:26.28,Dialogue,M,0000,0000,0000,,while also being preserved.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.94,0:13:28.48,Dialogue,B,0000,0000,0000,,However, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.48,0:13:31.65,Dialogue,B,0000,0000,0000,,How did the culprit walk in and out of the back door?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.65,0:13:33.95,Dialogue,Y,0000,0000,0000,,That's right! There was no one else passing by at that time!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.54,0:13:36.43,Dialogue,M,0000,0000,0000,,The culprit was walking under the eaves of the house...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.43,0:13:38.06,Dialogue,M,0000,0000,0000,,using the same method.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.06,0:13:41.46,Dialogue,M,0000,0000,0000,,That's why nobody saw them, and they never left any footprints.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.76,0:13:44.30,Dialogue,M,0000,0000,0000,,According to my investigation from this morning,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.11,0:13:46.39,Dialogue,M,0000,0000,0000,,coming out from back door,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.39,0:13:49.93,Dialogue,M,0000,0000,0000,,the snow on the right side leave footprints about 15cm deep.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.44,0:13:53.05,Dialogue,M,0000,0000,0000,,On the left side, only about 5cm deep.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.05,0:13:56.54,Dialogue,O,0000,0000,0000,,In short, the culprit was coming from the left side.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.54,0:13:57.62,Dialogue,M,0000,0000,0000,,And then,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.62,0:13:59.35,Dialogue,M,0000,0000,0000,,walking according to the path under the eaves of the house,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.07,0:14:04.19,Dialogue,M,0000,0000,0000,,the snow gets deeper at a certain point.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.74,0:14:08.20,Dialogue,B,0000,0000,0000,,A-And, where is it? {changed: "T-Then" to "A-And"}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.52,0:14:10.45,Dialogue,M,0000,0000,0000,,It's in front of your room,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.97,0:14:12.70,Dialogue,M,0000,0000,0000,,Akechi Eri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.58,0:14:16.75,Dialogue,R,0000,0000,0000,,W-What? {changed: "H-How can it be?" to current}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.75,0:14:18.21,Dialogue,Y,0000,0000,0000,,Eri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.11,0:14:23.70,Dialogue,M,0000,0000,0000,,Last night, after Asuka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} went to the hot spring,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.70,0:14:26.22,Dialogue,M,0000,0000,0000,,Eri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} left the open-air hot spring and went back to her room.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.83,0:14:29.93,Dialogue,M,0000,0000,0000,,By using the method described just now, she went to the shrine from the back door.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.93,0:14:34.72,Dialogue,M,0000,0000,0000,,She then killed Ema{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, who had been called out using Bandou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s name.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.18,0:14:40.40,Dialogue,I,0000,0000,0000,,It's true. By using that method, I {\i1}could{\i0} kill Ema{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.17,0:14:43.23,Dialogue,I,0000,0000,0000,,However, it's impossible to kill Asuka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.74,0:14:47.17,Dialogue,?,0000,0000,0000,,That's right. This hot spring was built on the mountainside.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.17,0:14:49.32,Dialogue,?,0000,0000,0000,,Using the same type of method is useless.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.37,0:14:53.73,Dialogue,B,0000,0000,0000,,And no one else passed by the recreation area.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.79,0:14:56.00,Dialogue,M,0000,0000,0000,,In fact...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.00,0:14:59.21,Dialogue,M,0000,0000,0000,,Asuka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was killed before Ema{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.61,0:15:05.96,Dialogue,M,0000,0000,0000,,Eri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} used the stun gun to make Asuka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} faint.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.35,0:15:08.81,Dialogue,M,0000,0000,0000,,She then took off Asuka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s clothes and killed her.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.81,0:15:10.91,Dialogue,M,0000,0000,0000,,After that, she moved the dead body to the location that already had obis placed...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.91,0:15:12.34,Dialogue,M,0000,0000,0000,,and threw everything into the hot spring.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.04,0:15:16.85,Dialogue,M,0000,0000,0000,,The holy knife was probably stolen just before that night.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.85,0:15:21.07,Dialogue,I,0000,0000,0000,,But if Ema{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was killed after Asuka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r},
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.07,0:15:24.86,Dialogue,I,0000,0000,0000,,why were the holy knife and the bandana, which had blood on them, found in the hot spring?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.30,0:15:26.80,Dialogue,Y,0000,0000,0000,,Y-You're right!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.80,0:15:28.44,Dialogue,Y,0000,0000,0000,,That doll is...!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.99,0:15:31.82,Dialogue,M,0000,0000,0000,,That was a trick using dry ice.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.78,0:15:39.25,Dialogue,M,0000,0000,0000,,By using small pieces of dry ice, you can fit the doll into the cracks in the ceiling.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.25,0:15:41.73,Dialogue,M,0000,0000,0000,,If the time it takes for the dry ice to evaporate was calculated beforehand,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.73,0:15:45.46,Dialogue,M,0000,0000,0000,,then one could make the doll drop down at will.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.46,0:15:48.09,Dialogue,R,0000,0000,0000,,So that's why the doll felt a bit icy cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.70,0:15:53.12,Dialogue,M,0000,0000,0000,,The reason Eri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} asked the owner to buy cakes every day...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.12,0:15:55.97,Dialogue,M,0000,0000,0000,,was to obtain the dry ice. {changed: "it's" to "was"}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.73,0:15:59.83,Dialogue,O,0000,0000,0000,,The doll can now be explained,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.83,0:16:01.48,Dialogue,O,0000,0000,0000,,but what about the holy knife and the bandana?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.48,0:16:04.59,Dialogue,I,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't go to the women's hot spring after 10:30pm. {change: "never" to "didn't" and "that" to "the"}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.59,0:16:08.15,Dialogue,M,0000,0000,0000,,You don't need to actually come here to be able to get those objects here.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.06,0:16:11.36,Dialogue,M,0000,0000,0000,,We will now have a real experiment.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.80,0:16:18.24,Dialogue,G,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, I understand!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.27,0:16:34.51,Dialogue,?,0000,0000,0000,,Th-This is...!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.99,0:16:36.06,Dialogue,M,0000,0000,0000,,These planks...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.06,0:16:40.72,Dialogue,M,0000,0000,0000,,were sent down the cliff from Eri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s room.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.72,0:16:43.02,Dialogue,M,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone, please imagine...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.59,0:16:46.98,Dialogue,M,0000,0000,0000,,the holy knife used to kill Ema{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r},
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.32,0:16:49.73,Dialogue,M,0000,0000,0000,,and the bandana which had traces of Ema{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.02,0:16:51.36,Dialogue,?,0000,0000,0000,,By using this method,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.36,0:16:53.61,Dialogue,?,0000,0000,0000,,even if you didn't come out of the room, you can still get them into the women's hot spring!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.61,0:16:55.74,Dialogue,O,0000,0000,0000,,When Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and the rest of you were bathing,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.18,0:16:57.54,Dialogue,O,0000,0000,0000,,you heard a splashing sound.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.54,0:16:59.16,Dialogue,O,0000,0000,0000,,That was the sound made when the sledding planks fell into the water.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.57,0:17:00.69,Dialogue,M,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, it was.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.69,0:17:02.86,Dialogue,M,0000,0000,0000,,Eri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was using this trick...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.87,0:17:05.16,Dialogue,M,0000,0000,0000,,to confuse us by assuming the wrong order of the victims murders...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.16,0:17:08.33,Dialogue,M,0000,0000,0000,,and to justify her alibi.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.64,0:17:09.51,Dialogue,O,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.51,0:17:12.13,Dialogue,O,0000,0000,0000,,where did the two important pieces of wood go to?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.45,0:17:16.72,Dialogue,G,0000,0000,0000,,Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, I've brought them here.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.83,0:17:18.68,Dialogue,?,0000,0000,0000,,These are...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.13,0:17:21.27,Dialogue,G,0000,0000,0000,,They're the other obis, which were stored in the storage room.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.27,0:17:23.31,Dialogue,G,0000,0000,0000,,I've already frozen them until they were very hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.76,0:17:25.63,Dialogue,M,0000,0000,0000,,Using water to soak the obis...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.63,0:17:28.77,Dialogue,M,0000,0000,0000,,and placing them outside the room for one night will let them freeze until they're as hard as ice.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.31,0:17:32.98,Dialogue,M,0000,0000,0000,,She used the obis, frozen, to replace these two pieces of wood.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.98,0:17:35.46,Dialogue,O,0000,0000,0000,,I see... If it's like this...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.22,0:17:40.83,Dialogue,O,0000,0000,0000,,If they fall into the hot spring, the obis will revert back to their original shapes.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.45,0:17:45.49,Dialogue,M,0000,0000,0000,,If there were two floating obis next to the dead body in the hot spring, it would be suspicious.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.49,0:17:48.37,Dialogue,M,0000,0000,0000,,That's why she put a few of the obis into the hot spring.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.37,0:17:51.46,Dialogue,M,0000,0000,0000,,Also, she placed a number of furisodes in the shrine.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.85,0:17:54.53,Dialogue,M,0000,0000,0000,,Imitating Furisode-Hannya's legend...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.53,0:17:57.97,Dialogue,M,0000,0000,0000,,was a trick to hide this method.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.30,0:18:04.31,Dialogue,I,0000,0000,0000,,That's an interesting deduction.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.67,0:18:06.81,Dialogue,I,0000,0000,0000,,Do you have any evidence?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.79,0:18:11.69,Dialogue,M,0000,0000,0000,,Please let everyone take a look at the bottom of your foot.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.28,0:18:14.19,Dialogue,M,0000,0000,0000,,Please ensure that you've shown it to everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.61,0:18:18.17,Dialogue,O,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, Eri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.84,0:18:21.12,Dialogue,I,0000,0000,0000,,It's fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.95,0:18:27.16,Dialogue,H,0000,0000,0000,,It seems I stepped on something sharp a little while ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.46,0:18:30.58,Dialogue,M,0000,0000,0000,,No, you got this when you were killing Ema{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.11,0:18:34.34,Dialogue,M,0000,0000,0000,,You stepped on the earring she dropped, and it left this scar.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.63,0:18:41.24,Dialogue,M,0000,0000,0000,,Last night, when we were preserving the crime scene,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.24,0:18:43.64,Dialogue,M,0000,0000,0000,,when I had everyone gathered and waiting in the living room,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.26,0:18:48.52,Dialogue,M,0000,0000,0000,,Eri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} said it'd be better to let everyone sit down, so we switched to the lobby.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.06,0:18:54.23,Dialogue,M,0000,0000,0000,,Eri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, your right foot's wound was still bleeding then, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.61,0:18:58.24,Dialogue,M,0000,0000,0000,,That's why you wouldn't take your slippers off in the living room.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.16,0:19:01.61,Dialogue,I,0000,0000,0000,,Do you have any evidence to prove that this wound was caused by that earring?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.95,0:19:04.45,Dialogue,C,0000,0000,0000,,I found the lost earring! {changed: "The lost earring was found by me!" to current}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.81,0:19:05.66,Dialogue,C,0000,0000,0000,,Look!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.79,0:19:08.45,Dialogue,R,0000,0000,0000,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.06,0:19:12.33,Dialogue,C,0000,0000,0000,,Even a single earring of this brand is worth 200 thousand yen.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.75,0:19:13.67,Dialogue,O,0000,0000,0000,,That means...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.67,0:19:15.69,Dialogue,O,0000,0000,0000,,We only need to examine whether it has traces of her blood or not!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.69,0:19:17.10,Dialogue,O,0000,0000,0000,,This is the evidence!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.75,0:19:20.59,Dialogue,I,0000,0000,0000,,Good job... finding it...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.59,0:19:24.97,Dialogue,C,0000,0000,0000,,Actually, this is the pendant borrowed from Harumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.31,0:19:36.32,Dialogue,I,0000,0000,0000,,I've lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.69,0:19:42.82,Dialogue,I,0000,0000,0000,,I'm the one who killed both of them...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.24,0:19:51.41,Dialogue,Y,0000,0000,0000,,Why?! Why did you do such an awful thing?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.42,0:19:52.92,Dialogue,Y,0000,0000,0000,,Eri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.92,0:19:56.09,Dialogue,M,0000,0000,0000,,It's not Eri... It's Chieri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.64,0:19:58.84,Dialogue,M,0000,0000,0000,,You hid your real name...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.71,0:20:02.26,Dialogue,M,0000,0000,0000,,because it's really rare to see the surname "Ake."
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.26,0:20:06.35,Dialogue,M,0000,0000,0000,,Thus, many people have wrongly regarded "Ake Chieri" to be "Akechi Eri."
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.79,0:20:10.00,Dialogue,M,0000,0000,0000,,I had an acquaintance of mine from the police station investigate for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.00,0:20:11.27,Dialogue,M,0000,0000,0000,,Chieri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.27,0:20:16.52,Dialogue,M,0000,0000,0000,,You're Sakurako{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s older sister, the one who committed suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.52,0:20:19.90,Dialogue,R,0000,0000,0000,,E-Eri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r} is Sakurako{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s older sister?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.63,0:20:24.44,Dialogue,M,0000,0000,0000,,You lost your parents in a fire when you were younger.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.44,0:20:28.91,Dialogue,M,0000,0000,0000,,Only the younger sister, Sakurako{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, was adopted by the Suzuka family.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.33,0:20:33.52,Dialogue,I,0000,0000,0000,,I'll tell you everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.52,0:20:35.51,Dialogue,I,0000,0000,0000,,When my younger sister committed suicide,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.51,0:20:38.18,Dialogue,I,0000,0000,0000,,I was working on writing novels in Boston.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.18,0:20:41.30,Dialogue,I,0000,0000,0000,,I was only informed of her death a year afterwards.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.35,0:20:44.25,Dialogue,I,0000,0000,0000,,Fragile Sakurako...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.25,0:20:47.88,Dialogue,I,0000,0000,0000,,had unexpectedly committed suicide just because she was accused of dealing drugs.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.88,0:20:51.18,Dialogue,I,0000,0000,0000,,I was so regretful and felt pity.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.87,0:20:55.19,Dialogue,I,0000,0000,0000,,Why didn't she discuss the matter with me?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.50,0:20:57.09,Dialogue,I,0000,0000,0000,,I'm her sister.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.34,0:21:00.69,Dialogue,I,0000,0000,0000,,She's my only relative.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.53,0:21:03.85,Dialogue,I,0000,0000,0000,,I couldn't forgive them. {changed: "can't" to "couldn't"}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.85,0:21:06.11,Dialogue,I,0000,0000,0000,,Sakurako seemed too miserable. {changed: "is to pity" to current}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.71,0:21:10.05,Dialogue,I,0000,0000,0000,,Then, taking this job as an excuse,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.05,0:21:14.79,Dialogue,I,0000,0000,0000,,I pretended to find my university's classmate, Yoriko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, in order to call both of them here.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.79,0:21:21.59,Dialogue,I,0000,0000,0000,,I imitated the legend of Furisode-Hannya's revenge in order to get revenge on them.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.26,0:21:25.84,Dialogue,M,0000,0000,0000,,Do you think Sakurako{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} is content with this? {changed: "With this, Sakurako-san will feel happy?" to current}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.13,0:21:30.67,Dialogue,M,0000,0000,0000,,Three people took part in this interview.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.67,0:21:37.76,Dialogue,M,0000,0000,0000,,If the only one who trusted Sakurako{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, Fugatsu Harumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, didn't show up,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.76,0:21:41.41,Dialogue,M,0000,0000,0000,,I wouldn't have learned about the fact that your younger sister committed suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.41,0:21:44.16,Dialogue,M,0000,0000,0000,,And, I wouldn't have accused you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.39,0:21:47.05,Dialogue,M,0000,0000,0000,,I can't stop to think that Sakurako{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.05,0:21:50.94,Dialogue,M,0000,0000,0000,,wanted to console you, the one who wanted to commit the crime,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.94,0:21:56.03,Dialogue,M,0000,0000,0000,,by letting Harumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and you meet each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.28,0:21:58.83,Dialogue,I,0000,0000,0000,,Harumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.83,0:22:02.00,Dialogue,M,0000,0000,0000,,Couldn't Sakurako{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s hope reach you,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.00,0:22:05.92,Dialogue,M,0000,0000,0000,,who was being possessed by Hannya?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.54,0:23:43.35,Dialogue,M,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Why am I here?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.19,0:23:46.36,Dialogue,M,0000,0000,0000,,This doesn't look good. {changed: "It's a bad omen." to current}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.40,0:23:48.24,Dialogue,M,0000,0000,0000,,I knew it. {changed: "Shit!" to current}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.23,0:23:54.25,Thoughts,C,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Uncle, just enjoy your hot spring bath and take a rest. {I think we should translate "Occhan" to Uncle - Light-}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.18,0:24:02.82,Thoughts,C,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}What are these murderous stares? {changed: fixed}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.91,0:24:04.44,Thoughts,C,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}And the mystery of Kago Island? {changed: fixed}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.78,0:24:10.22,Dialogue,M,0000,0000,0000,,Mouri Kogoro will hide it no more; the real Sakuma Shochu is the best! {changed: fixed}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.87,0:24:14.01,Dialogue,C,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, do you taste something weird in your mouth? {changed: fixed}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.57,0:24:17.15,Dialogue,M,0000,0000,0000,,The volcano erupted. It's probably the ash. {chaned: fixed}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.52,0:24:20.64,Dialogue,C,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong?!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.71,0:24:23.49,Thoughts,M,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}This is...! {changed: fixed}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.69,0:24:28.33,Dialogue,C,0000,0000,0000,,Next Conan: Kogoro Gets Drunk in Satsuma, Part 1!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.83,0:24:32.65,Dialogue,C,0000,0000,0000,,Next Conan's Hint!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.11,0:24:34.68,Dialogue,C,0000,0000,0000,,Picky way of making sake.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.46,0:24:36.72,Dialogue Top,C,0000,0000,0000,,Next time we'll be in Kago Island!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.56,0:24:38.19,Dialogue Top,C,0000,0000,0000,,Uncle will be eating something!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.19,0:24:39.56,Dialogue Top,C,0000,0000,0000,,What are we doing there?
